climbs.name: Rust in Peace
climbs.fa: Louie Anderson, Bart Groendycke, Todd Alston & James Aguirre, January 1991

content.description: Romp up the thin flake to it's end, do the crux, clip a bolt and make some slabby moves to the shared anchor at a small ledge/stance. One star out of five.
content.protection: Gear to 1", bolt, 2 bolt anchor/rap shared with Bloody Knuckles. All bolts are 3/8".
content.location: The right of three routes near the obvious reddish patch of rock.

content.description:
Although seldom done this high-quality line, which requires one to be adept at several styles of climbing and is played out on high quality stone, is sure to bring a smile to your face once you clip the anchors.

A thin slabby section with smallish edges (5.11) is found between the first two bolts on the lower apron and there's another crux (5.10+) higher as the angle steepens and you make some interesting moves up a headwall in a corner to gain a ledge with the anchors. Three stars out of five.
content.location: The left of three routes near the obvious reddish patch of rock.

climbs.name: Bloody Knuckles
climbs.fa: Louie Anderson, Bart Groendycke, Todd Alston & James Aguirre, January 1991

content.description: Thin slabbing on crisp edges past three bolts (crux between the second and third bolts) make this a decent diversion if in the area. Were this three or four times longer it would be a great route, but alas it's not. One star out of five.
content.location: The middle of three routes near the obvious reddish patch of rock.
